              <h3>Grid Basics</h3>

              <h6>Classes</h6>
              <ul>
                <li><code>row:</code> Creats a division of the page that will contain columns. This must be wrapped around columns.</li>
                <li><code>collapse:</code> Chain to a row class like the examples on this page show to remove default gutters.</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="row display" style="padding: 20px;"></div>

              <hr>

              <h3>Small Grid Columns</h3>

              <h6>Classes</h6>
              <p>By using only the small grid your design will hold its layout through all the breakpoints.</p>
              <ul>
                <li><code>column(s):</code> Used inside or rows to create columns in your layout, should be chained to other column classes.</li>
                <li><code>small-#:</code> "#" can be 1-12 . Tis controls the width of the column.</li>
                <li><code>small-offset-#:</code> "#" can be 1-10. Pushes columns over by altering margins and should be chained.</li>
                <li><code>small-centered:</code> Center a single column inside a row. This shoudl be chained to other column classes.</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="row display">
                <div class="small-3 columns">small-3</div>
                <div class="small-3 columns">small-3</div>
                <div class="small-3 columns">small-3</div>
                <div class="small-3 columns">small-3</div>
              </div>
              <div class="row display">
                <div class="small-3 columns">small-3</div>
                <div class="small-3 small-offset-6 columns">small-3 offset-6</div>
              </div>
              <div class="row display">
                <div class="small-6 small-centered columns">small-3 centered</div>
              </div>
<%= code_example '
<div class="row display">
