              <hr>

              <h3>Medium Grid Columns</h3>

              <h6>Classes</h6>
              <p>By using only the medium grid your columns will hold its layout through the large breakpoints and stack below the medium breakpoint.</p>
              <ul>
                <li><code>medium-#:</code> "#" can be 1-12. This controls the width of the column.</li>
                <li><code>medium-offset-#:</code> "#" can be 1-10. Pushes columns over by altering margins and should be chained.</li>
                <li><code>medium-centered:</code> Center a single column inside a row. This shoudl be chained to other column classes.</li>
                <li><code>medium-uncentered:</code> If you've set the small column to be centered and want to stop that for the medium breakpoint, use this class.</li>
                <li><code>medium-push-#:</code> "#" can be 1-11. Push the source ordering of content to the left for our medium breakpoint.</li>
                <li><code>medium-pull-#:</code> "#" can be 1-11. Pull the source ordering of content to the right for our medium breakpoint.</li>
              </ul>
